<subSubSection id="079E653C5352FF9CFEF384F9FB85FD42" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4F3B36B75352FF9CFEF384F9FB85FD42" blockId="12.[151,1437,433,748]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55352FF9CFEF384F9FE9CFDBA" bold="true" box="[199,308,506,532]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks</emphasis>
. These tiny specimens (1.0– 
<quantity id="887C9B525352FF9CFC4E84F9FD78FDBA" box="[634,720,506,532]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
dd) are referred to 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345352FF9CFD9A84F9FB1AFDBA" authorityName="Guille &amp; Vadon" authorityYear="1986" box="[942,1202,506,532]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Astrophiuridae" genus="Ophiophycis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="gloriensis">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55352FF9CFD9A84F9FB1AFDBA" box="[942,1202,506,532]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ophiophycis gloriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the SW Indian Ocean as they have a first LAP that extends to the disc margin, spiniform thorny arm spines, a star-shaped centrodorsal plate and 4 visible pairs of tentacle pores. They differ from the larger 
<typeStatus id="903F88155352FF9CFD978741FC7BFDF2" box="[931,979,578,604]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">type</typeStatus>
(
<quantity id="887C9B525352FF9CFDD68741FB92FDF2" box="[994,1082,578,605]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
dd) in having only one tentacle scale and one scale between the radial shields. These are distinguishing features of another species from St Helena, 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345352FF9CFEA38789FE42FD0A" authority="Mortensen, 1933 d" authorityName="Mortensen" authorityYear="1933" box="[151,490,650,676]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Astrophiuridae" genus="Ophiophycis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55352FF9CFEA38789FEA7FD0A" box="[151,271,650,676]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">O. gracilis</emphasis>
Mortensen, 1933d
</taxonomicName>
, which 
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465352FF9CFC0B8789FD55FD0A" author="Litvinova, N. M." box="[575,765,650,676]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="113 - 131" refId="ref32739" refString="Litvinova, N. M. (1981) Brittle-stars (Ophiuroidea). In: Benthos of the submarine mountains Marcus-Necker and adjacent Pacific regions. Academy of Science of the USSR. P. P. Shirshov Institute of Oceanology, pp. 113 - 131." type="book chapter" year="1981">Litvinova (1981)</bibRefCitation>
considers a juvenile of 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345352FF9CFA328789FF7AFD66" authority="Koehler, 1914" authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1914" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Astrophiuridae" genus="Ophiomisidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="speciosum">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55352FF9CFA328789FA86FD0A" box="[1030,1326,650,676]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ophiomisidium speciosum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465352FF9CFB008789FF7AFD66" author="Koehler, R." pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 173" refId="ref32434" refString="Koehler, R. (1914) A contribution to the study of ophiurans of the United States National Museum. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 84, 1 - 173 pls. 1 - 18. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 27414" type="journal article" year="1914">Koehler, 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345352FF9CFEE887ADFDACFD66" authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1914" box="[220,516,686,712]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Astrophiuridae" genus="Ophiomisidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="speciosum">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55352FF9CFEE887ADFDACFD66" box="[220,516,686,712]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ophiomisidium speciosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has also been reported from 
<collectingRegion id="8D40F8555352FF9CFD7187ADFC11FD66" box="[837,953,686,712]" country="French Southern Territories" name="Iles Kerguelen" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Kerguelen</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B465352FF9CFDF387ADFBF9FD66" author="Guille, A." box="[967,1105,686,712]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="67 - 87" refId="ref31484" refString="Guille, A. (1982) A new genus and species of ophiacanthid brittlestar (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from the Kerguelen Islands, with new taxonomic, biogeographic and quantitative data on the echinoderm fauna. Memoirs of the Australian Museum, 16, 67 - 87. https: // doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0067 - 1967.16.1982.359" type="journal article" year="1982">Guille 1982</bibRefCitation>
), south of the SPA. More data is required to resolve the relationship of 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345352FF9CFC6887D1FD42FD42" authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1901" box="[604,746,722,748]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Astrophiuridae" genus="Ophiophycis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55352FF9CFC6887D1FD42FD42" box="[604,746,722,748]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ophiophycis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="88844D345352FF9CFD1487D1FB85FD42" box="[800,1069,722,748]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Astrophiuridae" genus="Ophiomisidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA55352FF9CFD1487D1FC65FD42" box="[800,973,722,748]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ophiomisidium</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
